{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775867525870,"sessionID":"ses_2860ce4d3ffexYkB1hNwUAcFPJ","part":{"id":"prt_d79f3faec001jG063x6cCtN16E","messageID":"msg_d79f3f671001VK1m5FP63JsqYr","sessionID":"ses_2860ce4d3ffexYkB1hNwUAcFPJ","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867557003,"sessionID":"ses_2860ce4d3ffexYkB1hNwUAcFPJ","part":{"id":"prt_d79f4745c001vOSxVcj2BVXquT","messageID":"msg_d79f3f671001VK1m5FP63JsqYr","sessionID":"ses_2860ce4d3ffexYkB1hNwUAcFPJ","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_tool-5c89a7d43da44d79bdb14a3709b6fa91","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md","newString":"# Delta Specification: CLI Publish Command (AR-022)\n\n## Module: cmd/cli\n## Language: Python\n## Size: L\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Publish command options and defaults\n\n### Scenario: Publish with all default options\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL use default values: `workspace` = `\".\"`, `version` = `None`, `image_url` = `None`, `image_username` = `None`, `image_password` = `None`, `description` = `None`, `region` = `None`, `cloud_provider` = `None`, `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`, `node_port` = `None`, `replicas` = `None`, `namespace` = `None`, `verbose` = `False`\n\n### Scenario: Publish with custom workspace\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish -f /path/to/workspace`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL use `/path/to/workspace` as the workspace path\n\n### Scenario: Publish with custom version\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish --version v1.2.3`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL use `v1.2.3` as the version string\n\n### Scenario: Publish with custom provider\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish --provider k8s`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL use `k8s` as the provider instead of default `agentcube`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: AgentCube provider prerequisites validation\n\n### Scenario: AgentCube provider missing router_url\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube`\n- **WHEN** metadata lacks `router_url` in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print an error message requiring `router_url` to be set in metadata and exit with code `1`\n\n### Scenario: AgentCube provider missing workload_manager_url\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube`\n- **WHEN** metadata lacks `workload_manager_url` in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print an error message requiring `workload_manager_url` to be set in metadata and exit with code `1`\n\n### Scenario: AgentCube provider with both URLs present\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and metadata contains both `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`\n- **WHEN** publish proceeds\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL proceed with AgentRuntime CR deployment via `AgentCubeProvider`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Standard Kubernetes publish flow\n\n### Scenario: K8s provider successful deployment\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s` and Kubernetes client initializes successfully\n- **WHEN** publish proceeds\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL call `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`, then `wait_for_deployment_ready(..., timeout=120)`, and update metadata with deployment info\n\n### Scenario: K8s provider deployment readiness timeout\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s` and deployment does not become ready within 120 seconds\n- **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready` exceeds timeout\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL raise `RuntimeError` after recording the error in metadata and exit with code `1`\n\n### Scenario: K8s provider with custom node_port\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish --provider k8s --node-port 31000`\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called\n- **THEN** the Service SHALL be created with NodePort `31000` (within valid range 30000-32767)\n\n### Scenario: K8s provider with custom replicas\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish --provider k8s --replicas 3`\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called\n- **THEN** the Deployment SHALL be created with `replicas: 3`\n\n### Scenario: K8s provider with custom namespace\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish --provider k8s --namespace production`\n- **WHEN** publish proceeds\n- **THEN** resources SHALL be deployed to the `production` namespace\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Image preparation for publishing\n\n### Scenario: Local build mode with Docker push\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `local` and `image_url`, `image_username`, `image_password` are provided\n- **WHEN** `_prepare_local_image` runs\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL push the local image to the specified registry using credentials and return the pushed image URL\n\n### Scenario: Cloud build mode image URL\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `cloud` and `image_url` is provided\n- **WHEN** `_prepare_cloud_image` runs\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL return the provided `image_url` without attempting to push\n\n### Scenario: Local build mode without image credentials\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `local` but `image_username` or `image_password` is missing\n- **WHEN** publish attempts to push the image\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print an error message requiring image repository credentials and exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Publish command verbose logging\n\n### Scenario: Publish with verbose output\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish --verbose`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL enable detailed logging at `DEBUG` level for all publish operations\n\n### Scenario: Publish error with verbose flag\n- **GIVEN** an error occurs during publish and `verbose` is `True`\n- **WHEN** `_handle_error` processes the exception\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print the full traceback along with the error message\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Publish metadata update\n\n### Scenario: Successful publish metadata update\n- **GIVEN** publish completes successfully\n- **WHEN** `_update_publish_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL update `agent_metadata.yaml` with agent info including agent_id, endpoint URL, deployment timestamp\n\n### Scenario: Publish failure metadata update\n- **GIVEN** publish fails after partial operations\n- **WHEN** `_update_publish_metadata` runs with error info\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL update `agent_metadata.yaml` with error details and status\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Publish command error handling\n\n### Scenario: Publish with invalid workspace path\n- **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` runs\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print an error message indicating the workspace directory does not exist and exit with code `1`\n\n### Scenario: Publish with unparsable metadata\n- **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` contains invalid YAML or missing required fields\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print a validation error and exit with code `1`\n\n### Scenario: Publish with Kubernetes connection failure\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s` and Kubernetes cluster is unreachable\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider` attempts to connect\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print an error message indicating Kubernetes connection failure and exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n## Changes to Core System\n\n### CLI Typer command\n- Added `publish` subcommand with options: `workspace`, `version`, `image_url`, `image_username`, `image_password`, `description`, `region`, `cloud_provider`, `provider`, `node_port`, `replicas`, `namespace`, `verbose`\n\n### Runtime implementation\n- `PublishRuntime.publish()` method orchestrates image preparation and deployment\n- `_publish_cr_to_k8s()` handles AgentRuntime CR deployment for `agentcube` provider\n- `_publish_k8s()` handles standard Deployment/Service deployment for `k8s` provider\n- `_prepare_image_for_publishing()` delegates to local or cloud image preparation\n- `_update_publish_metadata()` updates agent metadata with deployment info\n\n### Service integrations\n- `DockerService.push_image()` for pushing images to registries\n- `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` for AgentRuntime CR creation\n- `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` for standard K8s resources\n\n## API Changes\n\n### CLI commands\n- New: `publish` command in `agentcube.cli.main`\n\n### Runtime classes\n- Updated: `PublishRuntime` with provider-aware deployment logic\n\n## Configuration Changes\n\n### Metadata fields\n- Existing `AgentMetadata` fields used: `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, `version`, `image`, `auth`, `region`, `agent_id`, `agent_endpoint`, `k8s_deployment`\n\n### Environment variables\n- Optional: `ROUTER_URL` and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` can be set via environment for AgentCube provider\n\n## Migration Notes\n\nNo breaking changes. The `publish` command is a new addition that integrates with existing metadata and runtime infrastructure.","oldString":"# Delta Spec for AR-022\n\n## Changes to Core System\n\n[To be filled during spec definition]\n\n## API Changes\n\n[To be filled during spec definition]\n\n## Configuration Changes\n\n[To be filled during spec definition]\n\n## Migration Notes\n\n[To be filled during implementation]"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md\n@@ -1,17 +1,182 @@\n-# Delta Spec for AR-022\n+# Delta Specification: CLI Publish Command (AR-022)\n \n+## Module: cmd/cli\n+## Language: Python\n+## Size: L\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: Publish command options and defaults\n+\n+### Scenario: Publish with all default options\n+- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish`\n+- **WHEN** the command executes\n+- **THEN** the CLI SHALL use default values: `workspace` = `\".\"`, `version` = `None`, `image_url` = `None`, `image_username` = `None`, `image_password` = `None`, `description` = `None`, `region` = `None`, `cloud_provider` = `None`, `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`, `node_port` = `None`, `replicas` = `None`, `namespace` = `None`, `verbose` = `False`\n+\n+### Scenario: Publish with custom workspace\n+- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish -f /path/to/workspace`\n+- **WHEN** the command executes\n+- **THEN** the CLI SHALL use `/path/to/workspace` as the workspace path\n+\n+### Scenario: Publish with custom version\n+- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish --version v1.2.3`\n+- **WHEN** the command executes\n+- **THEN** the CLI SHALL use `v1.2.3` as the version string\n+\n+### Scenario: Publish with custom provider\n+- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish --provider k8s`\n+- **WHEN** the command executes\n+- **THEN** the CLI SHALL use `k8s` as the provider instead of default `agentcube`\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: AgentCube provider prerequisites validation\n+\n+### Scenario: AgentCube provider missing router_url\n+- **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube`\n+- **WHEN** metadata lacks `router_url` in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n+- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print an error message requiring `router_url` to be set in metadata and exit with code `1`\n+\n+### Scenario: AgentCube provider missing workload_manager_url\n+- **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube`\n+- **WHEN** metadata lacks `workload_manager_url` in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n+- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print an error message requiring `workload_manager_url` to be set in metadata and exit with code `1`\n+\n+### Scenario: AgentCube provider with both URLs present\n+- **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and metadata contains both `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`\n+- **WHEN** publish proceeds\n+- **THEN** the CLI SHALL proceed with AgentRuntime CR deployment via `AgentCubeProvider`\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: Standard Kubernetes publish flow\n+\n+### Scenario: K8s provider successful deployment\n+- **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s` and Kubernetes client initializes successfully\n+- **WHEN** publish proceeds\n+- **THEN** the CLI SHALL call `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`, then `wait_for_deployment_ready(..., timeout=120)`, and update metadata with deployment info\n+\n+### Scenario: K8s provider deployment readiness timeout\n+- **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s` and deployment does not become ready within 120 seconds\n+- **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready` exceeds timeout\n+- **THEN** the CLI SHALL raise `RuntimeError` after recording the error in metadata and exit with code `1`\n+\n+### Scenario: K8s provider with custom node_port\n+- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish --provider k8s --node-port 31000`\n+- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called\n+- **THEN** the Service SHALL be created with NodePort `31000` (within valid range 30000-32767)\n+\n+### Scenario: K8s provider with custom replicas\n+- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish --provider k8s --replicas 3`\n+- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called\n+- **THEN** the Deployment SHALL be created with `replicas: 3`\n+\n+### Scenario: K8s provider with custom namespace\n+- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish --provider k8s --namespace production`\n+- **WHEN** publish proceeds\n+- **THEN** resources SHALL be deployed to the `production` namespace\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: Image preparation for publishing\n+\n+### Scenario: Local build mode with Docker push\n+- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `local` and `image_url`, `image_username`, `image_password` are provided\n+- **WHEN** `_prepare_local_image` runs\n+- **THEN** the CLI SHALL push the local image to the specified registry using credentials and return the pushed image URL\n+\n+### Scenario: Cloud build mode image URL\n+- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `cloud` and `image_url` is provided\n+- **WHEN** `_prepare_cloud_image` runs\n+- **THEN** the CLI SHALL return the provided `image_url` without attempting to push\n+\n+### Scenario: Local build mode without image credentials\n+- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `local` but `image_username` or `image_password` is missing\n+- **WHEN** publish attempts to push the image\n+- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print an error message requiring image repository credentials and exit with code `1`\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: Publish command verbose logging\n+\n+### Scenario: Publish with verbose output\n+- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish --verbose`\n+- **WHEN** the command executes\n+- **THEN** the CLI SHALL enable detailed logging at `DEBUG` level for all publish operations\n+\n+### Scenario: Publish error with verbose flag\n+- **GIVEN** an error occurs during publish and `verbose` is `True`\n+- **WHEN** `_handle_error` processes the exception\n+- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print the full traceback along with the error message\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: Publish metadata update\n+\n+### Scenario: Successful publish metadata update\n+- **GIVEN** publish completes successfully\n+- **WHEN** `_update_publish_metadata` runs\n+- **THEN** the CLI SHALL update `agent_metadata.yaml` with agent info including agent_id, endpoint URL, deployment timestamp\n+\n+### Scenario: Publish failure metadata update\n+- **GIVEN** publish fails after partial operations\n+- **WHEN** `_update_publish_metadata` runs with error info\n+- **THEN** the CLI SHALL update `agent_metadata.yaml` with error details and status\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Requirement: Publish command error handling\n+\n+### Scenario: Publish with invalid workspace path\n+- **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist\n+- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` runs\n+- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print an error message indicating the workspace directory does not exist and exit with code `1`\n+\n+### Scenario: Publish with unparsable metadata\n+- **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` contains invalid YAML or missing required fields\n+- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called\n+- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print a validation error and exit with code `1`\n+\n+### Scenario: Publish with Kubernetes connection failure\n+- **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s` and Kubernetes cluster is unreachable\n+- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider` attempts to connect\n+- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print an error message indicating Kubernetes connection failure and exit with code `1`\n+\n+---\n+\n ## Changes to Core System\n \n-[To be filled during spec definition]\n+### CLI Typer command\n+- Added `publish` subcommand with options: `workspace`, `version`, `image_url`, `image_username`, `image_password`, `description`, `region`, `cloud_provider`, `provider`, `node_port`, `replicas`, `namespace`, `verbose`\n \n+### Runtime implementation\n+- `PublishRuntime.publish()` method orchestrates image preparation and deployment\n+- `_publish_cr_to_k8s()` handles AgentRuntime CR deployment for `agentcube` provider\n+- `_publish_k8s()` handles standard Deployment/Service deployment for `k8s` provider\n+- `_prepare_image_for_publishing()` delegates to local or cloud image preparation\n+- `_update_publish_metadata()` updates agent metadata with deployment info\n+\n+### Service integrations\n+- `DockerService.push_image()` for pushing images to registries\n+- `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` for AgentRuntime CR creation\n+- `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` for standard K8s resources\n+\n ## API Changes\n \n-[To be filled during spec definition]\n+### CLI commands\n+- New: `publish` command in `agentcube.cli.main`\n \n+### Runtime classes\n+- Updated: `PublishRuntime` with provider-aware deployment logic\n+\n ## Configuration Changes\n \n-[To be filled during spec definition]\n+### Metadata fields\n+- Existing `AgentMetadata` fields used: `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, `version`, `image`, `auth`, `region`, `agent_id`, `agent_endpoint`, `k8s_deployment`\n \n+### Environment variables\n+- Optional: `ROUTER_URL` and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` can be set via environment for AgentCube provider\n+\n ## Migration Notes\n \n-[To be filled during implementation]\n\\ No newline at end of file\n+No breaking changes. The `publish` command is a new addition that integrates with existing metadata and runtime infrastructure.\n\\ No newline at end of file\n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md","before":"# Delta Spec for AR-022\n\n## Changes to Core System\n\n[To be filled during spec definition]\n\n## API Changes\n\n[To be filled during spec definition]\n\n## Configuration Changes\n\n[To be filled during spec definition]\n\n## Migration Notes\n\n[To be filled during implementation]","after":"# Delta Specification: CLI Publish Command (AR-022)\n\n## Module: cmd/cli\n## Language: Python\n## Size: L\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Publish command options and defaults\n\n### Scenario: Publish with all default options\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL use default values: `workspace` = `\".\"`, `version` = `None`, `image_url` = `None`, `image_username` = `None`, `image_password` = `None`, `description` = `None`, `region` = `None`, `cloud_provider` = `None`, `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`, `node_port` = `None`, `replicas` = `None`, `namespace` = `None`, `verbose` = `False`\n\n### Scenario: Publish with custom workspace\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish -f /path/to/workspace`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL use `/path/to/workspace` as the workspace path\n\n### Scenario: Publish with custom version\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish --version v1.2.3`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL use `v1.2.3` as the version string\n\n### Scenario: Publish with custom provider\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish --provider k8s`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL use `k8s` as the provider instead of default `agentcube`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: AgentCube provider prerequisites validation\n\n### Scenario: AgentCube provider missing router_url\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube`\n- **WHEN** metadata lacks `router_url` in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print an error message requiring `router_url` to be set in metadata and exit with code `1`\n\n### Scenario: AgentCube provider missing workload_manager_url\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube`\n- **WHEN** metadata lacks `workload_manager_url` in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print an error message requiring `workload_manager_url` to be set in metadata and exit with code `1`\n\n### Scenario: AgentCube provider with both URLs present\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and metadata contains both `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`\n- **WHEN** publish proceeds\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL proceed with AgentRuntime CR deployment via `AgentCubeProvider`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Standard Kubernetes publish flow\n\n### Scenario: K8s provider successful deployment\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s` and Kubernetes client initializes successfully\n- **WHEN** publish proceeds\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL call `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`, then `wait_for_deployment_ready(..., timeout=120)`, and update metadata with deployment info\n\n### Scenario: K8s provider deployment readiness timeout\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s` and deployment does not become ready within 120 seconds\n- **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready` exceeds timeout\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL raise `RuntimeError` after recording the error in metadata and exit with code `1`\n\n### Scenario: K8s provider with custom node_port\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish --provider k8s --node-port 31000`\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called\n- **THEN** the Service SHALL be created with NodePort `31000` (within valid range 30000-32767)\n\n### Scenario: K8s provider with custom replicas\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish --provider k8s --replicas 3`\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called\n- **THEN** the Deployment SHALL be created with `replicas: 3`\n\n### Scenario: K8s provider with custom namespace\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish --provider k8s --namespace production`\n- **WHEN** publish proceeds\n- **THEN** resources SHALL be deployed to the `production` namespace\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Image preparation for publishing\n\n### Scenario: Local build mode with Docker push\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `local` and `image_url`, `image_username`, `image_password` are provided\n- **WHEN** `_prepare_local_image` runs\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL push the local image to the specified registry using credentials and return the pushed image URL\n\n### Scenario: Cloud build mode image URL\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `cloud` and `image_url` is provided\n- **WHEN** `_prepare_cloud_image` runs\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL return the provided `image_url` without attempting to push\n\n### Scenario: Local build mode without image credentials\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `local` but `image_username` or `image_password` is missing\n- **WHEN** publish attempts to push the image\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print an error message requiring image repository credentials and exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Publish command verbose logging\n\n### Scenario: Publish with verbose output\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube publish --verbose`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL enable detailed logging at `DEBUG` level for all publish operations\n\n### Scenario: Publish error with verbose flag\n- **GIVEN** an error occurs during publish and `verbose` is `True`\n- **WHEN** `_handle_error` processes the exception\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print the full traceback along with the error message\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Publish metadata update\n\n### Scenario: Successful publish metadata update\n- **GIVEN** publish completes successfully\n- **WHEN** `_update_publish_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL update `agent_metadata.yaml` with agent info including agent_id, endpoint URL, deployment timestamp\n\n### Scenario: Publish failure metadata update\n- **GIVEN** publish fails after partial operations\n- **WHEN** `_update_publish_metadata` runs with error info\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL update `agent_metadata.yaml` with error details and status\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Publish command error handling\n\n### Scenario: Publish with invalid workspace path\n- **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` runs\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print an error message indicating the workspace directory does not exist and exit with code `1`\n\n### Scenario: Publish with unparsable metadata\n- **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` contains invalid YAML or missing required fields\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print a validation error and exit with code `1`\n\n### Scenario: Publish with Kubernetes connection failure\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s` and Kubernetes cluster is unreachable\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider` attempts to connect\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print an error message indicating Kubernetes connection failure and exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n## Changes to Core System\n\n### CLI Typer command\n- Added `publish` subcommand with options: `workspace`, `version`, `image_url`, `image_username`, `image_password`, `description`, `region`, `cloud_provider`, `provider`, `node_port`, `replicas`, `namespace`, `verbose`\n\n### Runtime implementation\n- `PublishRuntime.publish()` method orchestrates image preparation and deployment\n- `_publish_cr_to_k8s()` handles AgentRuntime CR deployment for `agentcube` provider\n- `_publish_k8s()` handles standard Deployment/Service deployment for `k8s` provider\n- `_prepare_image_for_publishing()` delegates to local or cloud image preparation\n- `_update_publish_metadata()` updates agent metadata with deployment info\n\n### Service integrations\n- `DockerService.push_image()` for pushing images to registries\n- `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` for AgentRuntime CR creation\n- `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` for standard K8s resources\n\n## API Changes\n\n### CLI commands\n- New: `publish` command in `agentcube.cli.main`\n\n### Runtime classes\n- Updated: `PublishRuntime` with provider-aware deployment logic\n\n## Configuration Changes\n\n### Metadata fields\n- Existing `AgentMetadata` fields used: `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, `version`, `image`, `auth`, `region`, `agent_id`, `agent_endpoint`, `k8s_deployment`\n\n### Environment variables\n- Optional: `ROUTER_URL` and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` can be set via environment for AgentCube provider\n\n## Migration Notes\n\nNo breaking changes. The `publish` command is a new addition that integrates with existing metadata and runtime infrastructure.","additions":170,"deletions":5},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775867556971,"end":1775867557000}}}}
